tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mild renal impairment (elevated creatinine), hypoglycemia, low HbA1c, metabolic acidosis (low COâ), and abnormal urinalysis with proteinuria, glycosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance. Findings suggest possible diabetic ketoacidosis or another metabolic disturbance, with renal involvement. Clinical correlation and further evaluation are recommended.
